cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a framework for optimization methods with primal-dual certificates, which is relevant to machine learning applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses convergence rates, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper mentions norm-regularized generalized linear models, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses TV-regularized problems, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
